sentences: Mah Damba (born Mah Sissoko in Bamako, Mali, 1965) is a traditional griot singer.

She recorded two solo albums, Nyarela (Buda/Musique du Monde) in 1997 and Djelimousso, Mali: The Voice of the Mande (Trema/Sony) in 2000, as contributed three tracks to The Divas from Mali (World Network) in 1998.

In 1999, she contributed vocals to one track on composer Jonathan Elias' international choral project, The Prayer Cycle.
